# CDF Key Extraction & Aliasing — workflow / Toolkit compliance

When editing anything under **`cdf_key_extraction_aliasing`** that can affect **deployed data workflows** or **Cognite Toolkit** assets (including `workflow_template/**`, `workflows/**`, `scripts/scope_build/**`, `functions/**` workflow IR or task payloads, `module.py`, `default.config.yaml`, UI flow/canvas compile paths, or `data_modeling/**` referenced by triggers), **do not treat the task complete until validations pass**.

## Required checks (run from module root)

Set **`MODULE`** = `modules/accelerators/contextualization/cdf_key_extraction_aliasing`. From **`cd "$MODULE"`**, set **`export PYTHONPATH="functions:scripts:$(pwd)"`** before **pytest** or **`scripts/validate_workflow_version_graph.py`** (those imports need `functions/` and `scripts/` on the path).

1. **Scope build + trigger parity (CI-equivalent gate)**  
   `cd "$MODULE" && python module.py build --check-workflow-triggers`  
   Exit code **0** only — this verifies generated **Workflow** / **WorkflowVersion** / **WorkflowTrigger** YAML match templates and hierarchy.

2. **Execution graph vs compiled IR**  
   `cd "$MODULE" && PYTHONPATH="functions:scripts:$(pwd)" python scripts/validate_workflow_version_graph.py`  
   Ensures **`workflow_template/workflow.execution.graph.yaml`** matches **`compiled_workflow`** from **`workflow.template.config.yaml`** (+ canvas merge rules used at build).

3. **Automated tests touching workflow/build**  
   At minimum:  
   `cd "$MODULE" && PYTHONPATH="functions:scripts:$(pwd)" python -m pytest tests/unit/scope_build/ -q`  
   If you changed **IR, execution graph, local runner, or fn_common workflow code**, also run the relevant **`tests/unit/cdf_fn_common/test_workflow*.py`** and **`tests/unit/local_runner/test_*workflow*.py`** (or the full unit suite under `tests/unit/` for that area).

## Toolkit project (when one exists in the workspace)

If the user’s branch includes or is wired into a **Cognite Toolkit** project (`cdf.toml` / `fusion.yaml` consuming this module): run **`cdf build`** (and **`cdf verify`** / project-documented verify steps) with the intended **profile** so template variables and module paths still resolve. Fix any build errors before merging.

## Detail & edge cases

For command variants, dry-run, when **`--force`** is required (scoped flow YAML only; execution graph refreshes every build), and CI ordering, read **`.cursor/skills/cdf-key-extraction-aliasing-workflow-validation/SKILL.md`**.
